meet kevin richard nelson, a 57-year-old protestant man, married for 27 years to his high school sweetheart, living in moline, illinois. kevin was born and raised in nearby rock island and spent his entire life in the quad cities area, deeply rooted in its community. a high school graduate, kevin attended united township high school and has always been proud of his local roots. he currently resides in a cozy $170,000 suburban single-family home in a quiet moline neighborhood with a small backyard, which he shares with his wife, two married daughters, and 9-year-old grandson who visits frequently, fostering a loving, family-oriented atmosphere.

kevin works as a maintenance supervisor at john deere, a major agricultural machinery plant in the region, for over 25 years, pulling in a household income of around $110,000 annually from his role. he's been fortunate to steadily work full-time, enjoying the security of health insurance and 401(k) matching. this economic stability and neighborhood cultural familiarity reinforce kevin's republican party affiliation and generally conservative ideology. as someone deeply embedded within his community, kevin recurrently encounters policy debates that impact job growth, social values, and the country's productive infrastructure—stuff that prudent policy making at every level of government holds sensitive.

as a regular attendee of religious services more than once a week at the moline presbyterian church, kevin incorporates faith in every aspect of life. strong in his born-again, evangelical beliefs, kevin thrives in a spirit-filled environment which fosters these values, especially as part of an umbrella organization that often collaborates with similar denominations nationwide.
